      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "name": "Custom Liquid",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "<style>\n/* ===== Layout ===== */\n.page-container {\n  max-width: 1100px;\n  margin: 0 auto;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n\n/* ===== Sections ===== */\n.section-bone {\n  margin-bottom: 48px;\n}\n\n.section-bone h2 {\n  font-size: 26px;\n  margin-bottom: 14px;\n}\n\n.section-bone h3 {\n  font-size: 20px;\n  margin-top: 22px;\n  margin-bottom: 10px;\n}\n\n.section-bone p {\n  margin-bottom: 12px;\n  line-height: 1.7;\n  color: #374151;\n}\n\n.section-bone ul,\n.section-bone ol {\n  margin: 14px 0 18px;\n  padding-left: 20px;\n}\n\n.section-bone li {\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\n}\n\n/* ===== Blockquote ===== */\n.blockquote {\n  margin-top: 18px;\n  padding: 14px 16px;\n  background: #f1f5f9;\n  border-left: 4px solid #4f6fae;\n  color: #334155;\n}\n\n/* ===== Comparison Table ===== */\n.comparison-table {\n  width: 100%;\n  margin-top: 20px;\n  border-collapse: separate;\n  border-spacing: 0;\n  background: #ffffff;\n  border-radius: 10px;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  box-shadow: 0 4px 14px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);\n}\n\n.comparison-table th {\n  background: #4f6fae;\n  color: #ffffff;\n  padding: 14px;\n  font-size: 15px;\n  text-align: center;\n}\n\n.comparison-table td {\n  padding: 14px;\n  font-size: 14px;\n  text-align: center;\n  border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;\n}\n\n.comparison-table td:first-child {\n  text-align: left;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  background: #f9fafb;\n}\n\n/* ===== FAQ ===== */\n.faq-item {\n  margin-bottom: 22px;\n  padding-bottom: 18px;\n  border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;\n}\n\n.faq-question {\n  font-size: 17px;\n  font-weight: 700;\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\n}\n\n.faq-answer {\n  font-size: 15px;\n  line-height: 1.7;\n  color: #374151;\n}\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"page-container\">\n\n  <section class=\"section-bone\">\n    <h2>What Are Bone Conduction Headphones & Earphones?</h2>\n    <p><strong>Bone conduction headphones or bone conduction earphones</strong> are a revolutionary type of audio device that transmit sound through your cheekbones, bypassing the eardrum entirely.</p>\n    <p>This technology lets you enjoy music while staying aware of your surroundings, making it ideal for runners, cyclists, and people with hearing concerns.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"section-bone\">\n    <h2>How Do Bone Conduction Headphones & Earphones Work?</h2>\n    <p>They use transducers placed on your cheekbones to send vibrations directly to the cochlea (inner ear), bypassing the eardrum.</p>\n    <p>This keeps your ear canal open for ambient awareness.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"section-bone\">\n    <h2>When Were Bone Conduction Headphones Invented?</h2>\n    <p>The concept of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bone_conduction\" target=\"_blank\">bone conduction</a> dates back to the 18th century. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludwig_van_Beethoven\" target=\"_blank\">Ludwig van Beethoven</a> explored it by biting a metal rod connected to his piano.</p>\n    <p>Modern consumer-grade bone conduction headphones became widely available in the early 2000s.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"section-bone\">\n    <h2>What Are the Benefits of Bone Conduction Headphones?</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Hear traffic and surroundings.</li>\n      <li><strong>Comfort:</strong> No ear pressure.</li>\n      <li><strong>Hygiene:</strong> No earwax build-up.</li>\n      <li><strong>Inclusive:</strong> Suitable for certain hearing loss.</li>\n      <li><strong>Multi-tasking:</strong> Stay connected while listening.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"section-bone\">\n    <h2>How to Use Bone Conduction Headphones?</h2>\n    <ol>\n      <li><strong>Position</strong> them on your cheekbones.</li>\n      <li><strong>Pair</strong> via Bluetooth.</li>\n      <li><strong>Adjust volume</strong> for clarity.</li>\n      <li>Do not place them inside your ears.</li>\n    </ol>\n    <div class=\"blockquote\"><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> A snug fit improves sound clarity.</div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"section-bone\">\n    <h2>Bone Conduction vs Traditional Headphones</h2>\n    <table class=\"comparison-table\">\n      <tr>\n        <th>Feature</th>\n        <th>Bone Conduction</th>\n        <th>Regular Headphones</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>Safety</td>\n        <td>Lets outside sound in</td>\n        <td>Blocks noise</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>Comfort</td>\n        <td>No ear pressure</td>\n        <td>Can cause fatigue</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>Sound Quality</td>\n        <td>Mids & highs focused</td>\n        <td>Full bass & clarity</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>Best For</td>\n        <td>Sports & awareness</td>\n        <td>Music immersion</td>\n      </tr>\n    </table>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"section-bone\">\n    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">1. Are Bone Conduction Headphones Safe?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">Yes, they are FDA-approved and safer for long listening sessions.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">2. Are bone conduction headphones bad for you?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">No, when used responsibly at moderate volume.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">3. Are bone conduction headphones better for hearing?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">Yes, they reduce strain on the eardrum.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">4. Can bone conduction headphones cause hearing loss?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">Only if used at extremely high volume for long durations.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">5. Can bone conduction headphones help with hearing loss?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">They help with conductive hearing loss but do not restore hearing.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">6. Can bone conduction headphones cause headaches?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">Rarely, and usually due to improper fit.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">7. When should bone conduction headphones be used?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">During workouts, commuting, office work, and outdoor activities.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">8. Are bone conduction headphones waterproof?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">Some models are waterproof; always check IP ratings.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">9. Can bone conduction headphones be used for swimming?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">Yes, IP68-rated models are suitable for swimming.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <div class=\"faq-question\">10. Can bone conduction headphones be used for phone calls?</div>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">Yes, most models include built-in microphones.</div>\n    </div>\n\n  </section>\n\n</div>",
